@node Introduction "Introduction to ExeDT"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}ExeDT@{ub} is a @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} subclass for loading and displaying Amiga executables. Once installed it will let all @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes} aware programs to recognize and load amiga-executables and view its contents as text.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements for ExeDT"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}ExeDT@{ub} requires AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher (@{i}datatypes.library @{ui}).
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation of ExeDT"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 Use supplied @{i}Installer @{ui}script to copy necessary files. If you go for "Manually Selectable" installation you will need to activate class by double-clicking on @{i}DEVS:DataTypes/Exe @{ui} icon or using @{i}AddDataTypes @{b}REFRESH @{ub}@{ui}from Shell.
@endnode

@node Configuration "Configuring operation of ExeDT"

  @{b}@{u}Configuration@{uu}@{ub}

 You can use a config file to customize operation of @{b}ExeDT@{ub} and thus appearance of the contens on screen. The config file is
  @{i}ENV:DataTypes/exe.prefs @{ui}
 The config file is a multi-line ASCII file. Each line could have one command word. Some Pararmeters will only cause an action on some executables. So e.g. only localizies programs sould have catalogs.

@{fg highlight}PARAMETERS@{fg text}
 Perhaps will follow in the next version ;-)
 Till this time, please use DTpref!

 You should use DTpref V4.0 or higher (look into the AmiNet for it) for configurating the @{b}ExeDT@{ub}. Here you have to set a tooltype in the DTpref-Icon which look like this one:
  @{b}DT=exe.datatype,DTpref@{ub}
 With DTpref V4.0 or higher you could also use the internal preferences setup of DTpref.
@endnode

@node Notes "ExeDT Notes"

  @{b}@{u}Notes@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}ExeDT@{ub} shows all informations about an executable.
@endnode

